_header: I Sir Hector most honorable that prince was of Troy
_description: On the Nine Worthies — 9 eight-line stanzas (ababbcbc)

LincolnArchK1.First Lines:
I ser Ector most honorable þat prynce was of Troyexix kyngys
                    att þat sege I slowe with myn handys…
LincolnArchK1.Last Lines:
…By thes ix worthi take hede þe most & þe
                    lesteFor welthe hele ne welefare ys but a theryfayre
LincolnArchK1.Note:
Headings, ‘Syr Hector of Troye’, ‘Julius
                    Cesare’. etc. above each stanza.

Turville-Petre,  Thorlac.
